                <p>The Norwegian economy has been affected by the global recession, but the downturn seems to be less severe than in most other countries. The implementation of extensive liquidity and credit policy actions, as well as expansionary fiscal and monetary policy measures, has stabilised the economy and provided stimulus to domestic demand. The economy has performed better than expected only a few months ago, and the outlook has improved.</p>
                
                
